Consider the following statements regarding Dear Money Policy:1.RBI raises the Bank Rate.2.Commercial banks can get the money at the higher rate of interest.3.RBI starts raising the CRR and sells the securities to Commercial Banks.Which of the statements given above is/are correct?,1 only,1 and 3 only,"1, 2 and 3",None,3,"Dear Money is when it is expensive to borrow money because of high real interest rates. For example, if bank rates are 10% and inflation is 6%. The effective real interest rate is 4% which is quite high. According to the loanable funds theory, this would require a rate of return on investment to be at least 4% of higher, to make investment worthwhile.
Bank rate is the rate charged by the central bank for lending funds to commercial banks. Bank rates influence lending rates of commercial banks. Higher bank rate will translate to higher lending rates by the banks. In order to curb liquidity, the central bank can resort to raising the bank rate and vice versa.
