"With reference to Bank rate and Repo rate, consider the following statements:1.While Bank rate is used for long term lending by RBI to commercial banks, Repo rate is used for short term.2.While lending at Bank rate requires government securities as collateral Repo rate does not require Governmentsecurities as collateral.Which of the above statements is/are correct?",1 only,2 only,Both 1 and 2 only,Neither 1 nor 2,1,"1.Bank Rate: In simple words Bank rate is the rate at which central bank (RBI) lends money to commercial banks for meeting shortfall for a long period without selling or buying any security.
