The FSR reflects the overall assessment on the stability of Indias financial system and its resilience to risks emanating from global and domestic factors. Besides, the Report also discusses issues relating to development and regulation of the financial sector. Beginning from June 2015 issue, a special thematic discussion is included in the FSRs brought out in June. Accordingly, this issue of FSR brings out a thematic discussion on An optimal configuration for the financial system-BanksversusMarket in the context of the progress towards making the Indian financial system more effective in supporting the economic growth.",Hint 160,1,1
