"Which of the following statement(s) correctly differentiates Hedge Fund and Mutual Fund?1.Hedge funds can make money even with share market going down, mutual fund cannot.2.Hedge Funds are riskier than Mutual Fund.3.Hedge Funds can issue P-notes by themselves while Mutual funds cannot.Select the correct answer using the code given below",1 and 3 only,2 and 3 only,"1, 2 and 3",1 and 2 only,4,"Statement 1 is correct. Hedge fund is a similar investment game, where High net worth individuals (HNI) pool their money into high risky game s to earn high return on investment.
But their trading-techniques are far more complex than mutual funds, hence Hedge funds can make money even with share market going down.
Statement 2 is correct. Theyprefe r to invest in risky bonds and shares (Because high risk=high return) e.g. Shares of Kingfisher and C graded Bonds of Somalian Government. And Mutual funds usually stick to shares and bonds of reliable companies.
Hence, Hedge Funds are more risky than Mutual Fund.
Statement 3 is incorrect. Hedge funds can no longer play in P-notes because SEBI classified foreign hedge funds into CAT III FPI.
What is CAT III FPI?
SEBI classified Foreign Portfolio Investors (FPI), on two criteria: 1.Risk profile: less risky – means better category
2.KYC compliance: better Know Your customer compliance means better category Category III:
1.Example Hedge funds (also known as alternative investment fund). 2.Inotherwords, highly risky and less KYC compliance type FII are put here. 3.Cannot issue participatory note s by themselves.",Hint 229,1,1
